Radiographers want the National Assembly to fast-track the enactment of the radiography laws to help regulate the use of Sh38billion Managed Equiment Service medical equipment.The Society of Radiographers in Kenya president Kenneth Kariuki urged MPs to pass the bill in the pre-publication phase. &ldquo;Radiographers are the users of the multibillion-shillings radiography equipment installed in 98 hospitals across the country by the government through MES.The bill will guarantee the public that the equipment is being used by regulated professionals,&rdquo; Kariuki said.The laws will govern the medics&rsquo; training and practice.This, Kariuki said, will ensure people get value for their money. &ldquo;There is need to strengthen professional associations,&rdquo; he said.